  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Key Inclusion Criteria:

          -  At least two (2) documented episodes of persistent atrial fibrillation during prior 3
             months

          -  Refractory, intolerant, or contraindicated to Class I or III anti-arrhythmic
             medications

          -  Left atrial diameter &lt; 6.0 cm

        Key Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Presence of structural heart disease

          -  NYHA Class IV.

          -  Ejection fraction &lt; 35%.

          -  History of myocardial infarction (MI) within the past three months.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
